urope’ in the 1930s. A legendary studio like this – and its story – has so far not been told to an English-speaking readership. This collection aims to correct this, presenting the studio’s rich history, its esteemed directors, and their most important films.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMotion picture studioszEurope, Central. 0aMotion pictureszEurope, Central. 4aFilm, Media, and Communication. 7aART / European.2bisacsh  aFilm history, Czech Film, Studio history.1 aBláhová, Jindřiška, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCzesany Dvořáková, Tereza, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHames, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerzogenrath, Bernd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHerzogenrath, Bernd, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aJohnson, Kevin B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Kevin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKokeš, Radomír D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOwen, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSkopal, Pavel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSorfa, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSweney, Matthew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSzczepanik, Petr, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aČesálková, Lucie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aŠašek, Michal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete 